SIMPLE: budding
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Budding
<hw>Bud"ding</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
or process of producing buds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A process of asexual
reproduction, in which a new organism or cell is formed by a protrusion
of a portion of the animal or vegetable organism, the bud thus formed
sometimes remaining attached to the parent stalk or cell, at other times
becoming free; gemmation. See <er>Hydroidea</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act or process of ingrafting one kind of plant
upon another stock by inserting a bud under the bark.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buddle</ent>⟦br⟧
